messages.content: Don't make assumptions about what values to plug into functions. Ask for clarification if a user request is ambiguous.
Remove phone number +12453344098 from my contact

I’m happy to help, but I’ll need the contact’s unique ID (person ID) or some additional details (such as the name linked to that phone number) to remove it from your contacts. Could you provide that information?
I don’t have any more information about that person.

I’m sorry, but to delete someone from your contacts I need at least one unique identifier—typically the person-ID that our contacts database assigns to each entry. If you aren’t sure which entry that number belongs to, you can:

• List your contacts so we can find the matching entry together, or  
• Tell me any other detail you remember about that person (name, note, relationship, etc.).

Let me know how you’d like to proceed!
I only have the phone number.

I’m sorry, but I don’t have a way to locate a contact solely from the phone number—you need the contact’s internal ID or at least some other identifying information (name, email, relationship, etc.) for me to remove it. If you’re able to look up the contact’s entry on your device to retrieve its ID or other details, let me know and I’ll delete it right away.
I don't have more information, just the number.

I’m unable to delete a contact unless I have its unique “person-ID.” Unfortunately, the tools available to me don’t let me look up that ID using only a phone number. 

If you can open your contacts list on your device and share either the person-ID or any other identifying detail (such as the saved name), I can remove the entry immediately. Otherwise, you might first need to locate the contact in your address book and share that ID with me.
